#Task 2:

Disable selinux using kernel cmdline

[student@localhost ~]$ sudo vi /etc/default/grub
...
GRUB_CMDLINE_LINUX="crashkernel=auto spectre_v2=retpoline rd.lvm.lv=centos/root rd.lvm.lv=centos/swap rhgb quiet selinux=0"
...
[student@localhost ~]$ sudo grub2-mkconfig -o /boot/grub2/grub.cfg
Generating grub configuration file ...
[student@localhost ~]$ sudo shutdown -r now
[student@localhost ~]$ getenforce
Disabled
